{"title":"IPH 49 - Summer suns are glowing","verses":[{"lines":["Summer suns are glowing"," over land and sea,"," happy light is flowing"," bountiful and free;"," everything rejoices"," in the mellow rays,","all earth’s thousand voices"," swell the psalm of praise."]},{"lines":["\fGod’s free mercy streaming"," over all the world,"," and his banner gleaming"," everywhere unfurled.","Broad and deep and glorious"," as the heaven above,"," shines in might victorious"," His eternal love."]},{"lines":["\f Lord, upon our blindness"," Your pure radiance pour;"," for your loving-kindness"," make us love you more.","And when clouds are drifting"," dark across the sky,"," then, the veil uplifting,"," Father, be close by."]},{"lines":["\f We will never doubt you."," though You veil Your light;"," life is dark without You,"," death with You is bright."," Light of light, shine o’er us"," on our pilgrim way;"," still go on before us"," to the endless day."]}],"chorus":"","CCLI":"William Walsham How, 1823-1897 CCLI 128675\r"}